# Rules for AI engineering / LLM pipeline work
# For ML/training projects, use python-ml-template instead

## Dependencies
- Add new dependencies to pyproject.toml under [project] dependencies

## Logging and config
- config.py handles both env loading and logging setup — it is the single bootstrap file
- Call config.setup() once at the top of main.py before anything else
- Use get_logger(__name__) from config in every module, never use print()

## LLM calls
- All LLM calls go through src/my_project/services/llm_client.py
- llm_client.py implements the BaseLLMClient ABC defined in models/
- Use OpenRouter as the default provider via OpenAI-compatible API (openai package, custom base_url)
- Default model is set in config.py as DEFAULT_MODEL and passed through — never hardcoded at call sites
- Model must always be a parameter — never hardcoded inside functions

## Data
- Use Pydantic BaseModel for all data passed between modules — no raw dicts
- All ABCs and shared interfaces are defined in models/ alongside Pydantic schemas

## Structure and design
- All external integrations (LLM, vector stores, embedders) sit in services/ and implement an ABC from models/
- This makes every external dependency swappable without touching pipeline code
- Pipelines in core/ only depend on ABCs, never on concrete service implementations
- Business logic → src/my_project/core/
- External integrations → src/my_project/services/
- Pydantic schemas + ABCs → src/my_project/models/
- Pure stateless helpers (string ops, parsing, formatting) → src/my_project/utils/
- Bootstrap (env + logging) → src/my_project/config.py
- Entry point → src/my_project/main.py

## Validation — run after every significant change
- Type check: pyright src/
- Smoke test: python tests/smoke_test.py
